-03-26T00:20:25", "channel": "system", "kind": "status", "title": "Complaint created", "detail": "Initial demand created and ready to draft.", "meta": {"stage": "initial_demand"}}, {"ts": "2026-03-26T00:20:33", "channel": "system", "kind": "decision", "title": "Drafted next step (draft_reply)", "detail": "Initial demand should be sent first.", "meta": {"thread_id": "LOCAL-company_support-1774484425925", "stage": "awaiting_company_response", "confidence": 0.86, "drafts": 1}}, {"ts": "2026-03-26T00:20:38", "channel": "email", "kind": "sent", "title": "Email sent", "detail": "Hello,\n\nI am contacting you regarding the following unresolved customer issue:\n\nMy first flight was delayed, I missed my connection, and I had to pay for hotel and meals. I request reimbursement of those costs.\n\nPlease review the issue, confirm the appropriate remedy, and provide a timeline for resolution.\n\nThank you.", "meta": {"thread_id": "19d2783ba94cf991", "gmail_msg_id": "19d2783ba94cf991", "gmail_thread_id": "19d2783ba94cf991", "subject": "[AGENT=company_support] Formal complaint and requested remedy"}}, {"ts": "2026-03-26T00:21:04", "channel": "email", "kind": "received", "title": "Email received from Boris Galitsky <bgalitsky@hotmail.com>", "detail": "Received, thank you.\r\nHere is a compensation voucher number 5498707534\r\n\r\n________________________________\r\nFrom: bg7550@gmail.com <bg7550@gmail.com>\r\nSent: Wednesday, March 25, 2026 8:20 PM\r\nTo: bgalitsky@hotmail.com <bgalitsky@hotmail.com>\r\nSubject: [AGENT=company_support] Formal complaint and requested remedy\r\n\r\nHello,\r\n\r\nI am contacting you regarding the following unresolved customer issue:\r\n\r\nMy first flight was delayed, I missed my connection, and I had to pay\r\nfor hotel and meals. I request reimbursement of those costs.\r\n\r\nPlease review the issue, confirm the appropriate remedy, and provide a\r\ntimeline for resolution.\r\n\r\nThank you.", "meta": {"thread_id": "19d2783ba94cf991", "subject": "Re: [AGENT=company_support] Formal complaint and requested remedy", "msg_id": "19d27841502fbe09"}}, {"ts": "2026-03-26T00:21:08", "channel": "system", "kind": "satisfaction", "title": "Satisfaction decision", "detail": "GPT fallback failed: Expecting value: line 1 column 1 (char 0)", "meta": {"thread_id": "19d2783ba94cf991", "verdict": "mixed_signals_needs_review", "gpt_used": true, "signals": {}}}, {"ts": "2026-03-26T00:21:08", "channel": "system", "kind": "decision", "title": "Drafted next step (draft_reply)", "detail": "Company appears to be offering a remedy; seek concrete confirmation and timeline.", "meta": {"thread_id": "19d2783ba94cf991", "stage": "resolutio   ć ć                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                             ųj! -3ü¼} bg7550@gmail.comCMP-20260326-005015{"complaint_id": "CMP-20260326-005015", "subject": "flight delay", "complaint_raw": "Hi, I'm writing to complain about missing my flight AA1847 from Chicago (ORD) to Miami (MIA) on March 15, 2026, because of an extremely long security line at Chicago O'Hare International Airport. I got to the airport at 1:30 PM, which was 2.5 hours before my 4:00 PM flightŌĆöway earlier than your recommended arrival timeŌĆöbut the security line at Terminal 3 barely moved for over 45 minutes because there weren't enough open lanes or staff. Even though I did everything right and arrived early, I still missed my flight because of the delay. This caused me to miss an important family event and cost me $450 to book a new last-minute flight. I'm asking if you can help me out with a travel voucher, a refund, or at least waive the rebooking fee as a goodwill gesture since I followed all the rules and still got stuck. I've attached my parking receipt and booking info, and I'd really appreciate your help sorting this out. Thanks.", "complaint_professional": "Hello,\n\nI am contacting you regarding the following unresolved customer issue:\n\nHi, I'm writing to complain about missing my flight AA1847 from Chicago (ORD) to Miami (MIA) on March 15, 2026, because of an extremely long security line at Chicago O'Hare International Airport. I got to the airport at 1:30 PM, which was 2.5 hours before my 4:00 PM flightŌĆöway earlier than your recommended arrival timeŌĆöbut the security line at Terminal 3 barely moved for over 45 minutes because there weren't enough open lanes or staff. Even though I did everything right and arrived early, I still missed my flight because of the delay. This caused me to miss an important family event and cost me $450 to book a new last-minute flight. I'm asking if you can help me out with a travel voucher, a refund, or at least waive the rebooking fee as a goodwill gesture since I followed all the rules and still got stuck. I've attached my parking receipt and booking info, and I'd really appreciate your help sorting this out. Thanks.\n\nPlease review the issue, confirm the appropriate remedy, and provide a timeline for resolution.\n\nThank you.", "user_email": "bg7550@gmail.com", "user_name": "Boris Galitsky", "created_at": "2026-03-26T00:50:15", "docs": [], "evidence_pack_pdf": null, "strategy": {"primary_goal": "refund/reimbursement", "acceptable_fallbacks": ["credit/voucher", "rebooking", "goodwill compensation"], "escalate_if": ["explicit denial", "no reply after follow-up", "ambiguous partial offer that does not satisfy demand"], "evidence_needed": ["receipts", "expense proof", "itinerary / ticket or booking reference"]}, "current_status_summary": "Company agreed to satisfy the demand. Complaint resolved.", "final_conclusion": "Company clearly offers a concrete monetary compensation of $300 within two days.", "auto_send_policy": "man      ╝  ę╝                                                              =                                                                          ­                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                             y                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                 Ķt -3üŽ/ bg7550@gmail.comCMP-20260327-000638{"complaint_id": "CMP-20260327-000638", "subject": "rude music teacher", "complaint_raw": "Hi, I'm writing to formally express my concern about the teaching approach of piano instructor David Chen, who has been giving weekly lessons to my child, Sofia, since January 2026. Over the past several sessions, Mr. Chen has repeatedly used dismissive and harsh languageŌĆösuch as telling Sofia she's \"not trying hard enough\" or sighing audibly when she makes simple mistakesŌĆöwhich has left her feeling anxious, discouraged, and reluctant to practice. We enrolled her in lessons to foster a love of music, but the current dynamic is having the opposite effect. I kindly request that [Music Academy Name] address this communication style and ensure instructors use patient, age-appropriate encouragement with young students. For follow-up, I understand the appropriate contact is the studio director at 209-270-9056. I hope we can work together to create a more positive and supportive learning enviro   µg -3ü╦] bg7550@gmail.comCMP-20260326-231821{"complaint_id": "CMP-20260326-231821", "subject": "Nurse comes at irregular times ", "complaint_raw": "Hi, I'm writing to formally complain about the inconsistent and unpredictable scheduling of the home visit nurse, Maria Gonzalez, who has been administering my injections. Over the past three weeks, visits have occurred at widely varying timesŌĆöranging from 8:15 AM to as late as 7:45 PMŌĆöwithout prior notice o